{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"pwd\ncat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\nThis folder contains papers gathered for:\n**Probing the Limits: Adversarial and OOD Robustness of Neural Thicket Ensembles**.\n\n## Primary Papers (downloaded)\n\n1. **Neural Thickets: Diverse Task Experts Are Dense Around Pretrained Weights** (\"'`2603.12228_Neural_Thickets_Diverse_Task_Experts_Are_Dense_Around_Pretrained_Weights_2026.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Yulu Gan, Phillip Isola\n   - Year: 2026\n   - arXiv: 2603.12228\n   - Why relevant: Core method family for thicket-style random perturbation experts.\n\n2. **Robust Deep Learning Ensemble against Deception** (`2009.06589_Robust_Deep_Learning_Ensemble_against_Deception_2020.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Wenqi Wei, Ling Liu\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2009.06589\n   - Why relevant: Joint adversarial + OOD defense via diversity-oriented ensemble verification.\n\n3. **Ensemble Adversarial Training: Attacks and Defenses** (`1705.07204_Ensemble_Adversarial_Training_Attacks_and_Defenses_2017.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Florian Tramèr et al.\n   - Year: 2017\n   - arXiv: 1705.07204\n   - Why relevant: Foundational ensemble-based adversarial training baseline.\n\n4. **Simple and Scalable Predictive Uncertainty Estimation using Deep Ensembles** (`1612.01474_Simple_and_Scalable_Predictive_Uncertainty_Deep_Ensembles_2016.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Balaji Lakshminarayanan et al.\n   - Year: 2016\n   - arXiv: 1612.01474\n   - Why relevant: Standard deep-ensemble uncertainty baseline used in OOD robustness work.\n\n5. **Out-of-Distribution Detection Using an Ensemble of Self Supervised Leave-out Classifiers** (`1809.03576_OOD_Detection_Ensemble_Self_Supervised_Leave_out_Classifiers_2018.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Apoorv Vyas et al.\n   - Year: 2018\n   - arXiv: 1809.03576\n   - Why relevant: OOD-specific ensemble detector baseline.\n\n6. **Enhancing Certifiable Robustness via a Deep Model Ensemble** (`1910.14655_Enhancing_Certifiable_Robustness_via_Deep_Model_Ensemble_2019.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Huan Zhang et al.\n   - Year: 2019\n   - arXiv: 1910.14655\n   - Why relevant: Certified robustness perspective for ensemble weighting.\n\n7. **Certifying Joint Adversarial Robustness for Model Ensembles** (`2004.10250_Certifying_Joint_Adversarial_Robustness_for_Model_Ensembles_2020.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Mainuddin Ahmad, David Evans\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2004.10250\n   - Why relevant: Formal certification for joint robustness of ensembles.\n\n8. **PEP: Parameter Ensembling by Perturbation** (`2010.12721_PEP_Parameter_Ensembling_by_Perturbation_2020.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Alireza Mehrtash et al.\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2010.12721\n   - Why relevant: Directly relevant perturbation-based ensemble construction mechanism.\n\n9. **Sequential Bayesian Neural Subnetwork Ensembles** (`2206.00794_Sequential_Bayesian_Neural_Subnetwork_Ensembles_2022.pdf`)\n   - Authors: Sanket Jantre et al.\n   - Year: 2022\n   - arXiv: 2206.00794\n   - Why relevant: Efficient uncertainty-aware ensemble variants.\n\n10. **Batch-Ensemble Stochastic Neural Networks for OOD Detection** (`2206.12911_Batch_Ensemble_Stochastic_NNs_for_OOD_2022.pdf`)\n    - Authors: Xiongjie Chen et al.\n    - Year: 2022\n    - arXiv: 2206.12911\n    - Why relevant: Parameter-sharing ensemble design with OOD emphasis.\n\n11. **On the Usefulness of Deep Ensemble Diversity for Out-of-Distribution Detection** (`2207.07517_Usefulness_of_Deep_Ensemble_Diversity_for_OOD_2022.pdf`)\n    - Authors: Guoxuan Xia, Christos-Savvas Bouganis\n    - Year: 2022\n    - arXiv: 2207.07517\n    - Why relevant: Directly evaluates how diversity affects OOD performance.\n\n12. **Hierarchical Pruning of Deep Ensembles with Focal Diversity** (`2311.10293_Hierarchical_Pruning_of_Deep_Ensembles_with_Focal_Diversity_2023.pdf`)\n    - Authors: Yanzhao Wu et al.\n    - Year: 2023\n    - arXiv: 2311.10293\n    - Why relevant: Diversity-aware pruning tradeoff between compute and robustness.\n\n## Additional Files\n\n- `paper_finder_results.json`: raw output from the paper-finder search.\n- `papers_metadata.json`: Semantic Scholar API retrieval log (including unavailable open PDFs).\n- `arxiv_search_results.json`: targeted arXiv query results.\n- `pages/`: chunked PDFs and manifests from the chunker workflow.\n\n## Note on Unavailable Papers\n\nOne highly relevant paper-finder hit had no easily accessible open PDF from this environment:\n- **DENL: Diverse Ensemble and Noisy Logits for Improved Robustness of Neural Networks (2023)**.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
